00:14:22,920 --> 00:14:27,324
So there are basically three scenes at three times a day in this one piece of art, and

208
00:14:27,364 --> 00:14:30,047
I will be talking a little later about how I do that as well.

209
00:14:32,451 --> 00:14:38,196
Again, it's not so much that I expect you to run out and do palette shift effects like this, or color cycling effects like this.

210
00:14:38,496 --> 00:14:44,041
It's just, there was so much more to do with a palette that you could control color by color,

211
00:14:44,382 --> 00:14:46,364
that you could fiddle with the positions of things,

212
00:14:47,444 --> 00:14:53,090
there was so much more you could do because the environment was small enough that you could actually think about it that way.

213
00:14:54,060 --> 00:15:00,286
