790
00:52:14,700 --> 00:52:16,261
the speed of the gradient isn't changing.

791
00:52:16,301 --> 00:52:18,122
That's all one gradient at one speed.

792
00:52:18,382 --> 00:52:21,103
But by putting that gradient in very short little segments,

793
00:52:21,523 --> 00:52:24,385
it only has to move, that color shift only has to move

794
00:52:24,445 --> 00:52:26,046
three pixels of vertical distance.

795
00:52:26,346 --> 00:52:28,047
Down here, that color shift needs to move

796
00:52:28,107 --> 00:52:30,348
five, 10 pixels of vertical distance.

797
00:52:30,748 --> 00:52:32,829
It has to all happen in the same period of time,

798
00:52:32,909 --> 00:52:34,610
so that color shift is gonna happen.

799
00:52:35,310 --> 00:52:38,591
faster in a long gradient than it is in a short gradient.

800
00:52:38,631 --> 00:52:41,792
So you're gonna use vertical stuff to control your speed.

801
00:52:42,152 --> 00:52:45,233
So you want the things at the top to be shorter vertically

802
00:52:45,673 --> 00:52:47,873
and the spaces at the bottom to be longer vertically

803
00:52:47,893 --> 00:52:50,834
while you fill it with that contour gradient

804
00:52:51,134 --> 00:52:53,354
so that your waterfall pours slowly over the lip

805
00:52:53,395 --> 00:52:55,035
and then picks up speed as it falls.

806
00:52:55,895 --> 00:52:57,816
Secondly, these little yellow bands in here

807
00:52:57,896 --> 00:53:00,336
are to bridge the seam between these gradients.

