811
00:53:11,623 --> 00:53:12,904
Then there's this sharp cutoff

812
00:53:13,164 --> 00:53:18,168
Between the last color in the gradient and the first color in the gradient and if you leave it that way there will be this

813
00:53:18,248 --> 00:53:26,535
Knife edge line where things flash in the middle of this otherwise smooth movement, so you actually need to fill those little yellow margins with a

814
00:53:27,116 --> 00:53:28,657
vertical gradient and put

815
00:53:29,938 --> 00:53:34,139
fill the top half with the last color of the gradient above it

816
00:53:34,259 --> 00:53:37,361
and fill the bottom half with the first color in the gradient below it

817
00:53:37,761 --> 00:53:42,323
so that there is never a point at which you just have a hard edge between one color and the next.

818
00:53:43,906 --> 00:53:45,727
So that's what I'm doing in these first four things.

819
00:53:45,787 --> 00:53:49,469
